              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Google says it can associate subdomains with the root domain when it understands they belong to the same organisation. In practice, SEO testing and ranking data consistently show that subdomains build authority more slowly than equivalent content on subfolders of the root domain.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
