              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. A subdomain can independently accumulate authority and outrank the root domain for specific queries. Many large sites have subdomains (support.example.com, docs.example.com) that rank above the main site for certain terms. This typically requires significant independent link building to the subdomain.</p></div></div>
